{"title": "What's next for Malaysia? Mahathir moves to shore up political clout", "tags": "asia", "timestamp": "2018-05-13", "content": "KUALA LUMPUR \u2022 Malaysia's newly sworn-in premier Tun Dr Mahathir Mohamad has set an aggressive tone for his new administration, promising a raft of reforms, pledges to investigate previous wrongdoings and top-level changes in the civil service.\nBehind the scenes, a more urgent campaign is taking shape to shore up his political clout within the Pakatan Harapan (PH) coalition that trounced the Barisan Nasional (BN) in the historic May 9 general election."}